<html>
    <head>
        <title>Hacktoberfest leaderboard</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <a href="https://github.com/ourtigarage/hacktoberfest-leaderboard"><img style="position: absolute; top: 0; right: 0; border: 0;" src="https://camo.githubusercontent.com/652c5b9acfaddf3a9c326fa6bde407b87f7be0f4/68747470733a2f2f73332e616d617a6f6e6177732e636f6d2f6769746875622f726962626f6e732f666f726b6d655f72696768745f6f72616e67655f6666373630302e706e67" alt="Fork me on GitHub" data-canonical-src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/github/ribbons/forkme_right_orange_ff7600.png"></a>
        <h1>Hello Hacktoberfest world !!!</h1>
        <h2>Leaderboard</h2>
        <% for member in leaderboard.members do %>
            <a href="<%=member.profile%>">
                <img height=44 width=44 src="<%=member.avatar%>"/><%=member.username%>
            </a>
            Contributions: <%= leaderboard.member_contributions(member.username).size %>
            <br/>
        <% end %>
        <br/>

        <h2>How to contribute</h2>
        If you want your name to be listed, you first need to make your first contribution.
        Fork <a href="https://github.com/ourtigarage/hacktoberfest-summit">this repository</a>, update the file
        <a href="https://github.com/ourtigarage/hacktoberfest-summit/blob/master/participants.md">participants.md</a> by adding your
        github username, and submit your first pull request.
        Once accepted, your name will appear in the leaderboard.<br/>
        <br/>
        You want to go further ? As you may have seen, this page looks like crap, right ?
        Feel free to help us making it fancier, improving the content, fixing any typpos,
        adding or improving features , etc ...<br/>
        <br/>
        Happy coding folks !!!
    </body>
</html>